# Workspace Filesystem Protocol

## Filesystem

The workspace is a plain git checkout. Resolve its root as the directory containing `AGENTS.md`;
read and write ordinary files there. No cloud-drive mount, no symlink alias.

Available to all models in Cursor; per `01-agent-controller.mdc`, only Claude writes.

## Claude — allowed without confirmation

- Read any workspace file to answer context questions
- Write artifacts to `05-artifacts/active/` (naming convention required)
- Update `06-context/project-context.md`, `session-log.md`, `artifact-registry.md`
- Update skills in `03-skills/` when explicitly requested
- Run `09-tools/compile-cursor-rules.py` to sync compiled outputs

## Claude — requires user confirmation

- Modifying `01-frameworks/` or `04-preferences/user-preferences.md`
- Modifying any file in `00-bootstrap/`
- Deleting or archiving any skill directory
- Writing to `.cursor/rules/` outside of the compile script

## Obsidian conventions (always preserve)

- `[[wikilinks]]` for internal links — graph depends on them
- YAML frontmatter on metadata-bearing notes
- Tags: lowercase + hyphenated
- Tasks: `- [ ]` open, `- [x]` done
- Artifact names: `context_descriptor_vN.N_YYYY-MM-DD.ext`
- Never delete — move to `_archive/`

## Compile script

Syncs context files → `AGENTS.md`. Run after changes to `06-context/` or `04-preferences/`.

```bash
cd "<workspace checkout>"   # the directory containing AGENTS.md
python3 09-tools/compile-cursor-rules.py
# watch mode:
python3 09-tools/compile-cursor-rules.py --watch
```
